## v1.2.0 (2026-06-15)

**Changed by:** ProjectHephaestus issue #1357 planning session (continued) — after confirming the
work was already on disk, the plan-loop reviewer returned NOGO (Grade D) on a plan that was
actually a retrospective status note, exposing a lesson v1.1.0 did not cover.
**Verification:** verified-local (the boundary/mypy/ruff gates ran GREEN this session, resolving
v1.1.0's "not run" caveats for those gates; the full `tests/unit/automation` suite still had no
reported pass/fail count, so the suite-wide claim stays conservative)

### What changed

- Added the core NEW lesson: even when the work is already on disk, the plan-loop demands a
  FORWARD-LOOKING plan. A "status note" (bullets describing what shipped + caveats) is a category
  error and gets NOGO'd (Grade D) on Completeness/Concreteness/Verification-Plan/Stage-Handoff —
  "on disk being correct does not rehabilitate the plan artifact itself."
- Added the stage-handoff lesson: never DEFER a checkable gate (boundary tests, mypy) to the
  reviewer as "follow-up"; run it during planning and cite it as completed.
- Added a When-to-Use trigger: "the plan-loop reviewer NOGO'd your plan as a 'status note' /
  retrospective."
- Added Verified-Workflow steps 9 (emit a forward-looking plan even for landed work) and 10 (run
  every gate yourself; mypy-duplicate-module and pytest `--no-cov` gotchas; subset-coverage is an
  artifact).
- Added 4 Failed Attempts rows: status-note-as-plan → NOGO; defer-gate-to-reviewer → stage-handoff
  failure; `pixi run mypy <paths>` → Duplicate module error; subset `pixi run pytest` without
  `--no-cov` → unrecognized `--cov`.
- Added a Results & Parameters subsection with the GREEN gate outputs (2 passed boundary; mypy
  clean on 402 files; ruff clean; 2449 lines; 25 stubs; preservation methods at :781/:880/:943/
  :1019) and the explicit note that mypy proves type-level DIP but NOT behavioral SRP.
- Extended the planner decision tree with the forward-plan-even-when-done branch and the
  subset/`--no-cov`/`mypy`-bare notes; added a second Verified On row for the NOGO→fix.
- Frontmatter: bumped `version` 1.1.0 → 1.2.0, kept `date` 2026-06-15, broadened `description`,
  kept `verification: verified-local`.

### Why

v1.1.0 captured "the work may already be done (merged OR uncommitted) — verify before planning."
It did not cover what to do with the PLAN ARTIFACT once you confirm the work is done. The #1357
session learned that the plan-loop still grades the artifact, not the disk: a descriptive status
note is NOGO'd as a category error, and deferring a runnable gate to the reviewer is a
stage-handoff failure. The fix is to emit a genuine forward-looking plan (design + files +
build order + per-criterion verification) and to run every gate yourself. The session ran the
previously-deferred boundary/mypy/ruff gates GREEN, which also upgrades v1.1.0's call-site DIP
inference to type-level proof.

